findings: The server header for the remote web server is: "Apache/2.4.7 (Ubuntu)".
The x-powered-by header for the target HTTP server is "PHP/5.5.9-1ubuntu4.24".
The remote Web server has a custom configuration, in which any not implemented methods that are invoked are defaulted to GET instead of returning a "Not Implemented" response.
The target site has a DNS wildcard configuration, the contents of "http://foobar.localhost:8080/" are equal to the ones of "http://localhost:8080/".
Fingerprinted this host as a *nix system. Detection for this operating system is weak, "if not windows then linux".
A Cross Site Scripting vulnerability was found at: "http://localhost:8080/pictures/search.php", using HTTP method GET. The sent data was: "query=" The modified parameter was "query".
Cross Site Request Forgery has been found at: http://localhost:8080/pictures/search.php

Cross Site Request Forgery has been found at: http://localhost:8080/pictures/view.php

A potential (most probably a false positive than a bug) buffer-overflow was found when requesting: "http://localhost:8080/calendar.php", using HTTP method GET. The data sent was: "date=AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA".

An unhandled error, which could potentially translate to a vulnerability, was found at: "http://localhost:8080/admin/index.php", using HTTP method GET. The sent data was: "page=" The modified parameter was "page".

An unhandled error, which could potentially translate to a vulnerability, was found at: "http://localhost:8080/users/sample.php", using HTTP method GET. The sent data was: "userid=" The modified parameter was "userid".

An unhandled error, which could potentially translate to a vulnerability, was found at: "http://localhost:8080/users/register.php", using HTTP method POST. The sent post-data was: "...username=..." which modifies the "username" parameter.

An unhandled error, which could potentially translate to a vulnerability, was found at: "http://localhost:8080/pictures/view.php", using HTTP method GET. The sent data was: "picid=" The modified parameter was "picid".
The URL: "http://localhost:8080/guestbook.php" returned an empty body, this could indicate an application error.
The URL: "http://localhost:8080/admin/index.php" returned an empty body, this could indicate an application error.
The URL: "http://localhost:8080/users/sample.php" returned an empty body, this could indicate an application error.
The URL: "http://localhost:8080/calendar.php" returned an empty body, this could indicate an application error.
The URL: "http://localhost:8080/pictures/search.php" returned an empty body, this could indicate an application error.
